EVENT_NARRATIVE: A tree fell on a moving car traveling south on Furnace Dock Road, in Cortlandt Westchester County, killing the driver and casing minor injuries to 2 passengers.
EPISODE_NARRATIVE: Strong winds on the backside of a vigorous Low over Southeast Canada downed a tree on a car in Westchester County, killing 1 person and injuring 2 others.

EVENT_NARRATIVE: Strong winds were responsible for the loss of power to 1,200 customers in Westchester County due to downed power lines and trees.
EPISODE_NARRATIVE: A strong low pressure system approached from the south.  A warm front passed to the north of the area.

EVENT_NARRATIVE: Strong winds were responsible for the loss of power to 1,200 customers in Westchester County due to downed power lines and trees.
EPISODE_NARRATIVE: A strong low pressure system approached from the south.  A warm front passed to the north of the area.

EVENT_NARRATIVE: A wind gust to 53 mph was reported by the public at 6 am.
EPISODE_NARRATIVE: A strong low pressure system approached from the south and caused strong wind gusts ranging from around 40 to 55 mph across the area.

EVENT_NARRATIVE: Wires were knocked down due to the strong winds in Crestwood, near the Read Avenue exit ramp off the Bronx River Parkway. In addition, trees were blocking the right lane southbound on the Hutchinson Rover Parkway.
EPISODE_NARRATIVE: Strong winds developed between a retreating offshore high pressure system and an approaching cold front.

EVENT_NARRATIVE: Numerous trees and power lines were knocked down due to the strong winds at Croton-on-Hudson.
EPISODE_NARRATIVE: Strong winds developed between a retreating offshore high pressure system and an approaching cold front.

EVENT_NARRATIVE: The ASOS at the White Plains Airport in Westchester county measured sustained winds of 38 mph at 955 pm.
EPISODE_NARRATIVE: An area of low pressure developed along a front just to the east and deepened rapidly producing strong winds across the region.

EVENT_NARRATIVE: At White Plains Airport in Westchester County, a gust of 55 mph was measured at 8:11 am, with a sustained wind of 41 mph also measured at 8:11 am.
EPISODE_NARRATIVE: Deep low pressure passed south and east of Long Island.

EVENT_NARRATIVE: A mesonet station around 1 mile west northwest of Sparta measured sustained winds of 37 mph at 7:02 am.
EPISODE_NARRATIVE: An area of low pressure deepened as it tracked to the northeast of the local region resulting in strong winds.

EVENT_NARRATIVE: The ASOS at White Plains Airport measured sustained winds of 38 mph at 10:03 am.
EPISODE_NARRATIVE: An area of low pressure deepened as it tracked to the northeast of the local region resulting in strong winds.

EVENT_NARRATIVE: A wind gust of 56 mph was observed at White Plains Airport at 4:00 pm.
EPISODE_NARRATIVE: Strong winds were observed behind a cold front.

EVENT_NARRATIVE: A mesonet reported a wind gust to 53 mph at 248 pm.
EPISODE_NARRATIVE: Strong to isolated high winds occurred ahead of an area of low pressure and associated frontal boundary.

EVENT_NARRATIVE: The ASOS at Westchester County Airport measured a wind gust up to 51 mph at 839 pm.

EVENT_NARRATIVE: Near Mamaroneck, a wind gust up to 50 mph was observed at 1227 pm.

EVENT_NARRATIVE: The ASOS at White Plains Airport measured wind gusts up to 55 mph at 911 am. In Mamaroneck, a mesonet station measure gusts up to 53 mph at 842 am.
EPISODE_NARRATIVE: Gusty northwest winds occurred behind a strong cold front.

EVENT_NARRATIVE: A mesonet station near Mamaroneck reported a wind gust up to 57 mph at 1236 am on the 30th.
EPISODE_NARRATIVE: A low pressure system rapidly intensified as it moved north, passing west of the local area.

EVENT_NARRATIVE: A mesonet station near Ossining measured a wind gust up to 53 mph at 1243 am on the 30th.
EPISODE_NARRATIVE: A low pressure system rapidly intensified as it moved north, passing west of the local area.

EVENT_NARRATIVE: A trained spotter reported two trees down on Feniminore Road with multiple tree limbs down. This was due to the winds and occurred around 1015 am in the town of Mamaroneck.
EPISODE_NARRATIVE: Strong gusty northwest winds occurred behind a strong cold front.

EVENT_NARRATIVE: The media reported a large tree down on a home on Nuber Avenue in Mount Vernon. This occurred around 715 am, and the home is uninhabitable. A mesonet station in Larchmong Harbor measure a 61 mph wind gust at 556 am. The instrument is elevated at a height of 40 ft. In the town of Tarrytown, route 119 was closed in both directions at the junction with I-287 due to downed wires around 9 am per media.
EPISODE_NARRATIVE: Strong winds occurred ahead of deep low pressure and associated warm front.

EVENT_NARRATIVE: A mesonet station in Larchmont Harbor reported a wind gust up to 55 mph at 551 am.

EVENT_NARRATIVE: The elevated mesonet station in Larchmont Harbor reported winds in excess of 50 mph shortly after midnight on the 16th of November.
EPISODE_NARRATIVE: Strong east to northeast winds developed across the region Thursday Night into early Friday morning, as an intensifying coastal storm tracked across the area.
